title: For Sale:  AR15 Custom Mid-length
location: NW Suburbs, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
Reduced price to $1850.00. Same information below applies

Up for sale is a AR15 in 5.56 that I assembled custom.  I had a few key goals in mind with this build.  Mid length gas system, lightweight, free floated, no pencil thin barrels, as short as legally possibly without the hassle of a pinned flash hider, fixed sights.  I am selling because it is an extra AR and the market is demanding these right now.  I have put somewhere between 40-50 rounds through the gun.  I followed a barrel break-in procedure for the first 15 or so rounds and the rest of the shooting was spent on finding a hand-load that shot well (see photos for details on this).

On to the components.  Where it matters I tried to give potential buyers a link to the original manufacturer site so that you can research the specifications for yourself.

- New Frontier Polymer Lower Receiver, Bullet Safety Markings - http://www.lw15.com
- Blackhole Weaponry Barrel 5.56, 16", 1:8 Twist, 1/2x28 Thread http://www.blackholeweaponry.com/catalog/product_info.php?cPath=21&products_id=60&osCsid=4a2c1b49dd5cb08e6d603fc2361127df
- A2 Flash Hider
- CMMG Lower Parts Kit
- Magpul MOE Grip
- Magpul MOE Stock with 6 position tube (Mil-spec)
- Mil-spec buffer and tube
- A3 Upper from Ammo Surplus, fit is super tight, no accu wedges or anything used
- M-16 Bolt Carrier Group. At the advice of a friend I used the heavier M-16 for the mid length system and love it
- Midwest Industries Gen2 SS-Series 15" Free float handguard - http://www.midwestindustriesinc.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=category.display&category_ID=450
- Low Profile Gas Block.  Barrel was properly dimpled, 2 set screws in gas block
- Daniel Defense A1.5 Sights - https://danieldefense.com/components-parts/sights/fixed-front-rear-sight-combo.html
- Vickers VCAS Sling - http://www.blueforcegear.com/vickers-combat-applications-sling/
- VLTOR Sling Endplate Mount - http://www.vltor.com/accessory.htm
- Heavy Duty Blackhawk QD Mount
- The MI handguard includes modular rails for the sides that I will include with the auction, the only one currently on the gun is the one with the QD mount for the sling.

Off the bench in about 17 degree weather I was able to shoot some impressive groups with the finer reticle using the DD sights that are on this gun.  While I would not guarantee it without testing, I have no doubt this is a sub-MOA weapon given some optics on the rifle.  Photos of my shooting results along with some chicken scratch notes on the powder/bullet combination are provided below.

A few extras that will be tossed in include a new in factory wrapping 30 round PMAG, Black.  I will also include a A1 and A2 sight adjustment tool for the front and rear sights and finally a Delron punch for assisting out the takedown pins, they are a nice tight fit.

Please do not send me low ball offers, I will respond when a reasonable offer is presented. A CCW or Permit to Purchase is required to buy this rifle.  I would prefer to transfer at Atomic in Bloomington or another FFL in the metro area. I will pay the transfer fee.

First introduced in our catalog in the spring of 96 the #1H or Heritage model has quickly become one of our most popular holsters.

title: For Sale:  .38 special 823 rounds of brass & brass/nickle plated wadcutter reloads. Satisfaction guaranteed!
postcontent:
Most of these are once fired reloads. There are a total of 823 rounds of .38 special brass or brass/nickle plated reloads. There are 744 rounds of brass/nickle plated wad cutters and79 rounds of brass flat nosed bullets for $200. These wadcutters are very accurate target loads that help save unnecessary wear on your bore. They make perfect round holes in the target and recoil is better than full metal jacketed loads.  Wadcutters have been used for decades by most expert shooters. Give them a try and if you are not 100% satisfied, I will refund your money for any unused portion.  

For those of you who have never seen or used wadcutters (WC), they are the most popular reloaded ammunition for target shooting. They may look a little weird, since most of the bullet is seated nearly all the way into the shell casing, but they weigh as much as FMJs and have comparable ballistics. Advantages: (1) conserve lead (2) conserve powder (3) create light loads which provide less recoil allowing for enjoyable extended practice sessions (which improves your accuracy) (4) punch nice holes in paper and lead is not as destructive to barrels compared to FMJs.  Any lead deposits left in the barrel can be easily removed with a brass brush. The last photo shows a box of wadcutters so you can see these are full size bullets.

title: For Sale:  The new law does not take effect until March, giving lawmakers some time to fix their oversight.
location: long island, New York, United States
postcontent:
The new law does not take effect until March, giving lawmakers some time to fix their oversight.



Due to slight oversight in New York’s new gun law, both police and private citizens will be banned from carrying high-capacity magazines.

According to TV station WABC, the New York Secure Ammunition and Firearms Enforcement Act, which bans magazines that carry more than seven rounds, does not provide an exemption for law enforcement officers, who typically carry handguns with a 15-round capacity.

The New York Patrolman's Benevolent Association President Patrick J. Lynch said in a press release Thursday that they are "actively working to enact changes to this law that will provide the appropriate exemptions from the law for active and retired law enforcement officers."

"As with many pieces of new legislation, there is a period shortly after enactment where omissions and unforeseen impacts become apparent that prompt a revision to the law," he said.

The law takes effect in March. The bill can be read here.

title: For Sale/Trade:  9mm S&W Model 3906
postcontent:
This is a 3906 and they were only made between 1989-1991. There were three variations: with adjustable sights, standard fixed sights and Novak fixed sights...somewhere around 3,000 are believed to of been made, with the Novak sighted examples being the scarcest. Luckily, S&W made parts interchangeable throughout much of it's 3rd Gen line, so parts & mags are still available...even factory direct. This 3906 is DA/SA, all stainless, full size and single stack. It weighs approximately 35oz and has a 4" barrel.

This gun came about right when the "wondernine" craze was really starting to spread, and is the reason for such a short life in the lineup. Sales of this 9+1 pistol couldn't compare to sales of S&W's 15+1 Model 5906...along with the other higher capacity 9's hitting the market. Both the 3906 and 5906 are known for their extreme reliability and ruggedness. 

Fast forward to today and many people are starting to appreciate flatter and lighter carry guns. Perhaps 10 rounds of 9mm really aren't that inadequate! Many people, even like myself with large hands, appreciate the ergonomics of this slim single stack gun compared to it's fatter 5906 doublestack  brother. S&W's 3rd Gen line as a whole is starting to gain more respect, as they were made to a higher standard and with better materials than the mass produced guns common today. 

These are great guns, but it just seems like I can't find too much love for the semi-automatic pistol :/ It came to me with some dried on super glue on the dust cover that I removed (previous owner glued on a laser sight, completely ridiculous), so there is a little evidence of where I polished it off, but it's not too noticeable as seen in the photos...other than that, this pistol appears close to new. I'd guess whoever owned it before me only fired a magazine or two and never carried it. Extremely clean, inside and out. Gun would come with (2) 9 round magazines and a  nwot Bianchi Model 6 IWB holster.

Not in a huge rush to sell, more interested in a trade really. I'm interested in older (1950-1996) S&W revolvers in .38, .357 & .22...blued or stainless. Sale price would be six hundred. I'm also passively looking for a Calico Liberty III pistol. I don't have to get rid of this gun and it took me quite a while to find, so I don't have any issue holding onto it. 

Looking specifically for, in order of precedence:

• 3" Model 65

+ All offers of blued or stainless .22/.38/.357 No-lock S&W's considered,   but the guns listed above will take precedence.




























Thanks for looking.
-Rob
